<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 6:01AM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG ACROSS PARTS OF THE Charlotte metro area and northern
UPSTATE...
Clear sky, light wind, and lingering moisture near the surface has
allowed for fog to develop across the southern Piedmont of North
Carolina and the northern Upstate of South Carolina, including
parts of metro Charlotte, early this morning. The fog was locally
dense from Shelby and Gastonia down to Rock Hill, Chester, and
over to Monroe. The fog may continue to expand a bit more through
sunrise, until a cold front pushes south across the area after
daybreak. Until that happens, be on the lookout for sharply
reduced visibility to one half mile or less if you have to drive
through sunrise.</description>
